snippet.textDisplay:
Legit, at this point, I feel it would have been much better to have Ryan Johnson make Star Wars 7. Blank slate, in a Star Wars universe, he could have done ANYTHING. Ultimately much of the blame falls on J.J. for setting up the story the way he did but Kathleen Kennedy must shoulder the majority of the blame for this car wreck, including the massive failing that was Solo.
At least we will get a new Star Wars trilogy in 2 years! Can't wait to see how well this will go! At this point the lore has been crippled by these movies to the point where I don't even care about the universe anymore. The basics have been shattered so thoroughly that no amount of retcon could even fix it for me.
Now people need to ask themselves this question; can you say that you like Star Wars if you dislike 2/3 of their flagship products (prequels and sequels). My answer at this point in time is No.

snippet.textDisplay:
I don't get why people say fans cant be pleased because they hated TLJ's new direction and also hate JJ doing rehashes. Had Rians new direction been watchable, I'd have loved it. His choices in it were just too stupid for me to be believable so it just pulled me out of the film.
JJ on the other hand just seems lazy AND creatively bankrupt. I gave Johnson a lot of hate for TLJ, but at least he gave a real attempt (tho he failed). Not sure where Star Wars films go from here. If they ever want to win me back, they'll have to set a trilogy 50,000 years away from the OT. I don't want to see a single ship or character I recognize. No fan service, no member berries.
